  "registerAsInspectorWithC2C": "Register as an Inspector with C2C",
  "iOVTitle1": "What is the purchase service by the Inspector?",
  "iOVTitle1Desc": "Vendors list their products on digital platforms in various conditions, providing detailed descriptions to accurately represent each item’s actual state and specifications. However, buyers often experience uncertainty and hesitation, which can hinder purchase completion.",
  "iOVTitle11Desc": "To overcome this challenge, the C2C company introduced the",
  "iOVTitle111Desc": "service — a first-of-its-kind solution in the individual transaction market. This service aims to strengthen and support buyer confidence, protect their rights, and ensure the credibility and transparency of product information and specifications displayed by vendors.",
  "iOVTitle2": "Who is the Inspector?",
  "iOVTitle2Desc": "A shopping inspector is an individual who possesses practical experience and the necessary skills in the field of inspecting a specific product or service. They have gained the trust of the C2C platform to work as a success partner within the list of shopping inspectors or expert inspectors. These inspectors carry out examination and verification processes for a product or service on behalf of the buyer within their geographical proximity. Additionally, the inspector may offer services as an inspector of a product listed by a seller, a shopping companion accompanying the buyer, or a delegated shopper tasked with purchasing a product or service on behalf of a buyer who lacks sufficient expertise or is hesitant to make a final purchase decision and pay for it.",
  "iOVTitle3": "When can the service be used?",
  "iOVTitle3Desc": "When viewing the details of any product, the buyer will find the \"Purchase via Inspector\" option as one of the applicable choices for purchasing the item. If the buyer selects this option, the inspection fee will be paid to the inspector chosen by the buyer, and the item will be reserved for inspection. The inspection request is then sent to the inspector, and the remaining procedures are completed among the inspector, the buyer, and the seller. Upon verification of the inspection and confirmation of all the information and specifications listed in the product details, the final decision to proceed with the purchase or cancel it rests with the buyer, who then rates the inspection process.",
  "iOVTitle4": "How to join the C2C Inspectors& shoppers Network?",
  "iOVTitle4Desc": "If you have sufficient experience and knowledge in the field of examining a commodity that is presented within the sections and classifications of goods circulating on the C2C platform, you can do the following steps:",
  "iOVTitle5": "Can the Inspector be assigned additional tasks?",
  "iOVTitle5Desc": "The inspector automatically performs the goods inspection service at the seller's location. The buyer has the right to request additional procedures and services from the inspector, provided that the inspector agrees to provide those services and the costs are paid directly to them. The C2C platform bears no responsibility for these additional tasks if they are not completed to the buyer's satisfaction.",
  "iOVTitle6": "Note",
  "iOVTitle6Desc": "The inspection and conversation process is conducted through a closed circuit with the concerned parties and is a reference for the C2C platform in the event of any unsatisfactory process for any party. We follow a zero tolerance policy for fraud or scams, and C2C has the right to block the seller or Inspector’s account if any of this is proven.",
